// donut.aria — Spinning ASCII Torus ("Can Aria run a donut?" — Yes.)
//
// Classic ASCII donut (Andy Sloane's donut.c) translated to Aria.
// Renders a rotating torus to the terminal using CPU math and a z-buffer.
// This is the first step toward the Utah Teapot renderer.
//
// Algorithm:
//   - Parametric torus: inner angle θ (tube), outer angle φ (ring)
//   - Two rotation angles A (x-axis) and B (y-axis) animate each frame
//   - For each (θ,φ) point: compute 3D coords, rotate, perspective-project
//   - ASCII luminance char from surface normal · light direction
//   - Write full frame buffer (with embedded newlines) in one syscall per frame
//
// Press Ctrl+C to exit.

use "../../stdlib/string_convert.aria".*;
use "../../stdlib/print_utils.aria".*;

// ── Runtime helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
extern func:aria_math_sin         = flt64(flt64:x);
